  "text": "compounds [CITATION_1] . Large datasets with experimentally characterized labeled data are quite valuable for constructing accurate models and libraries, so these tend to be closed-source and company-owned. Most current molecular generation applications utilize a subset of ZINC or ChEMBL molecules. For this purpose, we propose a biological molecule benchmark set refined from the ZINC database.",
